{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775887348744,"sessionID":"ses_284dfcc5effelRcCZBetUi7cYX","part":{"id":"prt_d7b2273c90014Ave7gc7KUb9Ul","messageID":"msg_d7b210343001ewXiWfVA902IOX","sessionID":"ses_284dfcc5effelRcCZBetUi7cYX","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-7282a5d955f34ac984d5456663ee6c7f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-033/delta-spec.md","content":"# Delta Spec: AR-033 — Makefile 构建目标体系\n\n**Module:** `root`  \n**Language:** Makefile  \n**Size:** M\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nDefine a comprehensive Makefile build target system for AgentCube, providing unified build interface across all binaries (workloadmanager, router, picod, agentd, agentctl, agentcube, agentsandbox), quality gates (lint, test, coverage), Docker image targets, and developer-friendly `make help` documentation.\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: Build targets for all binaries\n\nThe Makefile SHALL provide individual and aggregate build targets for all Go binaries.\n\n#### Scenario: Aggregate build target\n- **GIVEN** `Makefile` defines `build` target\n- **WHEN** `make build` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL compile all binaries:\n  - `bin/workloadmanager` from `./cmd/workloadmanager`\n  - `bin/router` from `./cmd/router`\n  - `bin/picod` from `./cmd/picod`\n  - `bin/agentd` from `./cmd/agentd`\n  - `bin/agentctl` from `./cmd/agentctl`\n  - `bin/agentcube` from `./cmd/agentcube`\n  - `bin/agentsandbox` from `./cmd/agentsandbox`\n\n#### Scenario: Single binary build targets\n- **GIVEN** `Makefile` defines per-binary targets\n- **WHEN** `make build-workloadmanager` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL compile only `bin/workloadmanager`\n- **WHEN** `make build-router` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL compile only `bin/router`\n- **WHEN** `make build-picod` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL compile only `bin/picod`\n- **WHEN** `make build-agentd` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL compile only `bin/agentd`\n- **WHEN** `make build-agentctl` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL compile only `bin/agentctl`\n- **WHEN** `make build-agentcube` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL compile only `bin/agentcube`\n- **WHEN** `make build-agentsandbox` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL compile only `bin/agentsandbox`\n\n#### Scenario: Default target\n- **GIVEN** `Makefile` defines `all` target\n- **WHEN** `make` is executed without target\n- **THEN** it SHALL execute `build` target (same as `make all`)\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Test targets\n\nThe Makefile SHALL provide unit test, coverage, and race detector targets.\n\n#### Scenario: Unit test target\n- **GIVEN** `Makefile` defines `test` target\n- **WHEN** `make test` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL run `go test -v ./...`\n- **AND** output SHALL be verbose per-package\n\n#### Scenario: Coverage test target\n- **GIVEN** `Makefile` defines `test-coverage` target\n- **WHEN** `make test-coverage` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL run `go test -coverprofile=coverage.out ./...`\n- **AND** `go tool cover -html=coverage.out -o coverage.html` SHALL generate HTML report\n- **AND** terminal SHALL display coverage percentage summary\n\n#### Scenario: Race detector test target\n- **GIVEN** `Makefile` defines `test-race` target\n- **WHEN** `make test-race` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL run `go test -race ./...`\n- **AND** race conditions SHALL be detected and reported\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Quality gate targets\n\nThe Makefile SHALL provide lint, format, vet, and codegen verification targets.\n\n#### Scenario: Lint target\n- **GIVEN** `Makefile` defines `lint` target\n- **WHEN** `make lint` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL run `golangci-lint run ./...`\n- **AND** linter version SHALL match `GOLANGCI_LINT_VERSION` variable\n\n#### Scenario: Format target\n- **GIVEN** `Makefile` defines `fmt` target\n- **WHEN** `make fmt` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL run `go fmt ./...`\n- **AND** all Go files SHALL be formatted per Go standards\n\n#### Scenario: Vet target\n- **GIVEN** `Makefile` defines `vet` target\n- **WHEN** `make vet` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL run `go vet ./...`\n- **AND** suspicious constructs SHALL be reported\n\n#### Scenario: Codegen verification target\n- **GIVEN** `Makefile` defines `gen-check` target\n- **WHEN** `make gen-check` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL:\n  - Run code generation commands (e.g., `go generate ./...`)\n  - Compare generated files with committed files\n  - Fail if generated output differs from committed version\n\n#### Scenario: Copyright header target\n- **GIVEN** `Makefile` defines `gen-copyright` target\n- **WHEN** `make gen-copyright` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL add/update copyright headers in all Go files\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Docker build targets\n\nThe Makefile SHALL preserve and extend Docker build targets for single-arch and multi-arch builds.\n\n#### Scenario: Single-arch Docker build targets\n- **GIVEN** `Makefile` defines Docker build targets\n- **WHEN** `make docker-build` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL build `$(IMAGE_REPO)/workloadmanager:$(VERSION)`\n- **WHEN** `make docker-build-router` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL build `$(IMAGE_REPO)/router:$(VERSION)`\n- **WHEN** `make docker-build-picod` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL build `$(IMAGE_REPO)/picod:$(VERSION)`\n- **WHEN** `make docker-build-all` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL build all three images sequentially\n\n#### Scenario: Multi-arch Docker buildx targets\n- **GIVEN** `Makefile` defines buildx push targets\n- **WHEN** `make docker-buildx-push` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL build and push `$(IMAGE_REPO)/workloadmanager:$(VERSION)` for `linux/amd64,linux/arm64`\n- **WHEN** `make docker-buildx-push-router` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL build and push router image for multi-arch\n- **WHEN** `make docker-buildx-push-picod` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL build and push picod image for multi-arch\n\n#### Scenario: Docker build arguments\n- **GIVEN** Dockerfile requires build arguments\n- **WHEN** docker build is executed\n- **THEN** `TARGETOS` and `TARGETARCH` SHALL be passed as `--build-arg`\n- **AND** default values SHALL be `linux` and `amd64`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: E2E test targets\n\nThe Makefile SHALL provide targets for Kind-based end-to-end testing.\n\n#### Scenario: E2E run target\n- **GIVEN** `Makefile` defines `e2e` target\n- **WHEN** `make e2e` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL call `test/e2e/run_e2e.sh`\n- **AND** Kind cluster SHALL be created if not exists\n- **AND** AgentCube SHALL be deployed via Helm\n- **AND** E2E tests SHALL be executed\n\n#### Scenario: E2E setup target\n- **GIVEN** `Makefile` defines `e2e-setup` target\n- **WHEN** `make e2e-setup` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL:\n  - Create Kind cluster\n  - Build and load Docker images\n  - Deploy AgentCube via Helm\n  - Wait for pods to be ready\n\n#### Scenario: E2E clean target\n- **GIVEN** `Makefile` defines `e2e-clean` target\n- **WHEN** `make e2e-clean` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL delete Kind cluster\n- **AND** all cluster resources SHALL be removed\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Install targets\n\nThe Makefile SHALL provide targets to install binaries to `$GOPATH/bin` or custom prefix.\n\n#### Scenario: Install all binaries\n- **GIVEN** `Makefile` defines `install` target\n- **WHEN** `make install` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL copy all binaries from `$(BINDIR)` to `$(INSTALL_PREFIX)`\n- **AND** `$(INSTALL_PREFIX)` default SHALL be `$GOPATH/bin`\n\n#### Scenario: Install single binary\n- **GIVEN** `Makefile` defines per-binary install targets\n- **WHEN** `make install-picod` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL install only `picod` binary\n- **WHEN** `make install-agentcube` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL install only `agentcube` binary\n\n#### Scenario: Custom install prefix\n- **GIVEN** user specifies custom prefix\n- **WHEN** `make install INSTALL_PREFIX=/usr/local/bin` is executed\n- **THEN** binaries SHALL be installed to `/usr/local/bin`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Clean targets\n\nThe Makefile SHALL provide targets to remove build artifacts.\n\n#### Scenario: Clean all artifacts\n- **GIVEN** `Makefile` defines `clean` target\n- **WHEN** `make clean` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL remove:\n  - `bin/` directory\n  - `coverage.out` file\n  - `coverage.html` file\n\n#### Scenario: Clean test artifacts only\n- **GIVEN** `Makefile` defines `clean-test` target\n- **WHEN** `make clean-test` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL remove only coverage files\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Cross-compile targets\n\nThe Makefile SHALL provide targets for native cross-compilation without Docker.\n\n#### Scenario: Linux AMD64 cross-compile\n- **GIVEN** `Makefile` defines `build-linux-amd64` target\n- **WHEN** `make build-linux-amd64` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL compile with `GOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64`\n\n#### Scenario: Linux ARM64 cross-compile\n- **GIVEN** `Makefile` defines `build-linux-arm64` target\n- **WHEN** `make build-linux-arm64` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL compile with `GOOS=linux GOARCH=arm64`\n\n#### Scenario: Darwin AMD64 cross-compile\n- **GIVEN** `Makefile` defines `build-darwin-amd64` target\n- **WHEN** `make build-darwin-amd64` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL compile with `GOOS=darwin GOARCH=amd64`\n\n#### Scenario: Darwin ARM64 cross-compile\n- **GIVEN** `Makefile` defines `build-darwin-arm64` target\n- **WHEN** `make build-darwin-arm64` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL compile with `GOOS=darwin GOARCH=arm64`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Help target\n\nThe Makefile SHALL provide formatted help output listing all targets with descriptions.\n\n#### Scenario: Help target output\n- **GIVEN** `Makefile` defines `help` target\n- **WHEN** `make help` is executed\n- **THEN** output SHALL be formatted as:\n  ```\n  Usage: make <target>\n  \n  Build targets:\n    build              Build all binaries\n    build-workloadmanager  Build workloadmanager binary\n    build-router           Build router binary\n    ...\n  \n  Test targets:\n    test               Run unit tests\n    test-coverage      Run tests with coverage report\n    ...\n  \n  Quality targets:\n    lint               Run golangci-lint\n    fmt                Format Go files\n    ...\n  ```\n\n#### Scenario: Target documentation in comments\n- **GIVEN** each target needs description\n- **WHEN** Makefile is written\n- **THEN** each target SHALL have comment in format `## <description>`\n- **AND** `help` target SHALL parse these comments\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Variable system\n\nThe Makefile SHALL define configurable variables with sensible defaults.\n\n#### Scenario: Image repository variable\n- **GIVEN** `IMAGE_REPO` variable is defined\n- **THEN** default SHALL be `ghcr.io/volcano-sh/agentcube`\n- **AND** syntax SHALL be `IMAGE_REPO ?= ghcr.io/volcano-sh/agentcube`\n\n#### Scenario: Version variable\n- **GIVEN** `VERSION` variable is defined\n- **THEN** default SHALL be derived from `git describe --tags --always --dirty`\n- **AND** fallback SHALL be `latest` if git fails\n\n#### Scenario: Bindir variable\n- **GIVEN** `BINDIR` variable is defined\n- **THEN** default SHALL be `bin/`\n- **AND** user SHALL be able to override with `make build BINDIR=out/`\n\n#### Scenario: Go version variable\n- **GIVEN** `GO_VERSION` variable is defined\n- **THEN** value SHALL be `1.24` (or current project version)\n- **AND** CI workflows SHALL reference this variable\n\n#### Scenario: Linter version variable\n- **GIVEN** `GOLANGCI_LINT_VERSION` variable is defined\n- **THEN** value SHALL be `1.64.7`\n- **AND** CI workflows SHALL reference this variable\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Phony target declarations\n\nThe Makefile SHALL declare all non-file targets as `.PHONY`.\n\n#### Scenario: Phony declarations\n- **GIVEN** targets do not produce files\n- **WHEN** Makefile is written\n- **THEN** `.PHONY` SHALL declare:\n  - `all`, `build`, `build-*` targets\n  - `test`, `test-coverage`, `test-race` targets\n  - `lint`, `fmt`, `vet`, `gen-check` targets\n  - `e2e`, `e2e-setup`, `e2e-clean` targets\n  - `install`, `install-*` targets\n  - `clean`, `clean-*` targets\n  - `docker-build-*`, `docker-buildx-*` targets\n  - `help` target\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: CI workflow integration\n\nThe Makefile targets SHALL be referenced by GitHub Actions workflows.\n\n#### Scenario: CI build workflow reference\n- **GIVEN** `.github/workflows/main.yml` runs build verification\n- **WHEN** workflow executes build step\n- **THEN** it SHALL use `make build`\n- **AND** not use inline `go build` commands\n\n#### Scenario: CI lint workflow reference\n- **GIVEN** `.github/workflows/lint.yml` runs linting\n- **WHEN** workflow executes lint step\n- **THEN** it SHALL use `make lint`\n\n#### Scenario: CI coverage workflow reference\n- **GIVEN** `.github/workflows/test-coverage.yml` runs coverage\n- **WHEN** workflow executes coverage step\n- **THEN** it SHALL use `make test-coverage`\n\n#### Scenario: CI E2E workflow reference\n- **GIVEN** `.github/workflows/e2e.yml` runs E2E tests\n- **WHEN** workflow executes E2E step\n- **THEN** it SHALL use `make e2e` and `make e2e-clean`\n\n---\n\n## Constants Summary\n\n| Constant | Value | File | Purpose |\n|----------|-------|------|---------|\n| `IMAGE_REPO` | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh/agentcube` | Makefile | Docker image repository |\n| `DEFAULT_VERSION` | `git describe --tags --always --dirty` | Makefile | Version derivation |\n| `VERSION_FALLBACK` | `latest` | Makefile | Version when git fails |\n| `TARGETOS` | `linux` | Makefile | Default target OS |\n| `TARGETARCH` | `amd64` | Makefile | Default target architecture |\n| `GO_VERSION` | `1.24` | Makefile | Go toolchain version |\n| `GOLANGCI_LINT_VERSION` | `1.64.7` | Makefile | Linter version |\n| `BINDIR` | `bin/` | Makefile | Binary output directory |\n| `INSTALL_PREFIX` | `$GOPATH/bin` | Makefile | Install destination |\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies Summary\n\n| Package | Version | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| `go` | `1.24+` | Go toolchain |\n| `golangci-lint` | `1.64.7` | Linting tool |\n| `docker` | `>=20.10` | Container builds |\n| `docker buildx` | `>=0.8` | Multi-arch builds |\n| `kind` | `>=0.20` | E2E test cluster |\n| `helm` | `>=3.8` | E2E chart deployment |\n| `git` | `>=2.30` | Version tagging |\n\n---\n\n## File Changes Summary\n\n| File | Action | Description |\n|------|--------|-------------|\n| `Makefile` | Modified | Major rewrite: add categorized targets, help system, cross-compile support, variable system |\n| `.github/workflows/main.yml` | Modified | Update to use `make build` instead of inline commands |\n| `.github/workflows/lint.yml` | Modified | Update to use `make lint` |\n| `.github/workflows/test-coverage.yml` | Modified | Update to use `make test-coverage` |\n| `.github/workflows/e2e.yml` | Modified | Update to use `make e2e`, `make e2e-clean` |\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- proposal.md — AR-033 proposal with scope and implementation checklist\n- GNU Make Manual — https://www.gnu.org/software/make/manual/\n- Go Build Modes — https://go.dev/cmd/go/#hdr-Build_modes\n- golangci-lint — https://golangci-lint.run/\n- Kind — https://kind.sigs.k8s.io/\n- ci-cd/design.md — Existing workflow targets\n- deployment/design.md — Docker build targets\n- test/e2e/run_e2e.sh — E2E test orchestration\n\n---\n\n## Validation Checklist\n\n- [ ] `make build` compiles all 7 binaries\n- [ ] `make build-picod` compiles only picod\n- [ ] `make test` runs all unit tests with verbose output\n- [ ] `make test-coverage` generates coverage.html\n- [ ] `make test-race` runs with race detector\n- [ ] `make lint` runs golangci-lint with correct version\n- [ ] `make fmt` formats all Go files\n- [ ] `make vet` runs go vet\n- [ ] `make gen-check` verifies codegen output\n- [ ] `make docker-build` builds workloadmanager image\n- [ ] `make docker-build-router` builds router image\n- [ ] `make docker-build-picod` builds picod image\n- [ ] `make docker-build-all` builds all images\n- [ ] `make docker-buildx-push-*` targets work for multi-arch\n- [ ] `make e2e` runs E2E tests via Kind\n- [ ] `make e2e-clean` deletes Kind cluster\n- [ ] `make install` installs binaries to `$GOPATH/bin`\n- [ ] `make install-picod` installs only picod\n- [ ] `make clean` removes bin/ and coverage files\n- [ ] `make build-linux-amd64` cross-compiles for Linux\n- [ ] `make build-linux-arm64` cross-compiles for ARM64\n- [ ] `make build-darwin-*` cross-compiles for macOS\n- [ ] `make help` shows formatted target list\n- [ ] `.PHONY` declarations include all non-file targets\n- [ ] Variables use `?=` syntax for overrides\n- [ ] CI workflows reference Make targets instead of inline commands"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-033/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-033/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775887348714,"end":1775887348740}}}}
